      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH) benchmarked against predicate device. Secondary QoIs include volume-averaged scalar stress and Lagrangian particle exposure time. All QoIs directly inform worst-case operating condition identification. Traceability to clinical endpoint established through published power-law hemolysis correlation (Giersiepen et al.)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
